> Yeah, I like metric but I still prefer my beer measured in pints.<p>Its funny.  Orwell was against the metric system, so there is a small amusing scene in 1984 where on the proles (an old man) in a bar complains that he hates liters of beer.<p><pre><code>    &quot;&#x27;Ark at &#x27;im! Calls &#x27;isself a barman and don&#x27;t know what a pint is! Why, a pint&#x27;s the &#x27;alf of a quart, and there&#x27;s four quarts to the gallon. &#x27;Ave to teach you the A, B, C next.&quot;

    &quot;Never heard of &#x27;em,&#x27; said the barman shortly. &#x27;Litre and half litres - that&#x27;s all we serve. There&#x27;s the glasses on the shelf in front of you.&quot;

    &quot;I likes a pint,&quot; persisted the old man. &quot;You could &#x27;a drawed me off a pint easy enough. We didn&#x27;t &#x27;ave these bleeding litres when I was a young man.&quot;</code></pre>
